# Build context for apps/{api,web,admin}/Dockerfile is the REPO ROOT, and each
# one does `COPY . .` — so anything not excluded here is baked into a published
# image. Keep this list tight: it is the only thing standing between local
# working-tree litter and GHCR.
#
# Unlike .gitignore, a bare name here is NOT "match at any depth": patterns are
# matched against the whole context-relative path, so `src` and `/src` both mean
# root-level only. Reach for `**/` when you really do want any depth — and never
# for `src` (that would eat apps/api/src). Verify with:
#   docker build -f apps/api/Dockerfile -t t . && docker run --rm t find /app -maxdepth 1

# ---------- dependencies & build output (installed/regenerated in-image) ----------
node_modules
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.next
**/.expo
**/*.tsbuildinfo
# Prisma client: the Dockerfile runs `prisma generate` itself, and a fresh clone
# never has this, so a host-generated copy (darwin engines) must not leak in.
packages/db/generated

# ---------- VCS & CI ----------
.git
.gitignore
.github

# ---------- secrets ----------
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
.mcp.json
apps/mobile/play-service-account.json

# ---------- agent / local tooling litter ----------
# .claude/worktrees holds a checked-out git worktree per agent branch — a full
# second copy of the source tree each, unrelated to the branch being built.
.claude
graphify-out
claude-memory.tgz

# ---------- host cwd-fallback litter (contained REAL member uploads) ----------
# A root-level src/ is NOT part of the repo — nothing under it is tracked. It
# only appears when the API is run with cwd=repo-root, which makes the
# MEDIA_DIR/CERT_FILES_DIR fallbacks in apps/api/src/{media,certificates}/
# *.config.ts resolve to <root>/src/... and write member avatars there.
# Root-anchored on purpose: apps/api/src (the actual API source, including the
# bundled certificate TTFs) must NOT match.
/src

# ---------- mobile native builds (~2.3 GB; rebuilt by EAS, never served) ----------
apps/mobile/android
apps/mobile/ios

# ---------- docs & local reports (not runtime) ----------
docs
*.md
!README.md
*.pdf
*.pptx

# ---------- os / logs / test output ----------
**/.DS_Store
**/*.log
**/coverage
